// error_vf.br — variable or function not found
// triggered when a called variable or function cannot be resolved.

// 1. return the variable or function name that was not found
// 2. check:
//    - variables.br — is the variable defined under the correct block?
//    - functions.br — is the function listed with correct name and path?
// 3. suggest most likely cause:
//    - name misspelled at call site
//    - entry missing from variables.br or functions.br
//    - wrong entry point used (br{f} called but needed br{v})
//    - function name not lowercase
// 4. do not continue the original script

return; pt; "b-rite error — variable or function not found. check variables.br or functions.br. confirm the entry exists and is correctly named. all names must be lowercase or camelCase."
